id: pm-9qcr
title: "GH-507: recovery suggested_retry appends <value> to missing boolean EXTENSION flags (contract arity ignored)"
description: "When an extension command throws a structured CommandError whose remediation names a declared boolean flag (SDK command contract declares --allow-empty with no value_name), pm correctly identifies the missing flag but renders it value-taking in recovery.suggested_retry: '--allow-empty \"<value>\"'. Expected bare '--allow-empty'. The flag renders correctly as boolean in help and contract metadata — only recovery suggestion generation ignores the extension contract's arity. This is the extension-contract sibling of GH-500/pm-6y58 (FIXED via PR#502 for built-in flag tables): the arity fix does not consult SDK/extension command contracts. Observed with pm-cli 2026.7.10 + pm-todos 'todos sync'."
type: Issue
status: in_progress
priority: 3
tags[5]: agent-ux,cli,error-recovery,extensions,gh-issue
